%*! conditional_hasValue(Expression)

Signifies that an expression has a value.

This means there exists some value and that value is neither `none` nor `bad`.

Args:
    - Expression: The [Expression] for which it is being determined whether it has a value.
*%

%*! conditional_hasNoValue(Expression)

Signifies that an expression does not have a value.

This means that the value of the expression is `none`.

Args:
    - Expression: The [Expression] for which it is being determined whether it does not have a value.
*%